    "number": 20825,
    "state": "closed",
    "locked": false,
    "title": "[Bugfix] Fix a couple PPLX+CUTLASS MoE bugs",
    "user": {
      "login": "ElizaWszola",
      "id": 26595727,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI2NTk1NzI3",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/26595727?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/ElizaWszola",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/following{/other_user}",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/gists{/gist_id}",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "user_view_type": "public",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "Fix two bugs that prevented CUTLASS MoE to run with PPLX:\n\n1. PPLX's All To All dispatch and combine functions require `topk_ids` to have the type `uint32`. Since we never expect elements of `topk_ids` to be negative when running with PPLX, this can be resolved with reinterpret casting the current signed `int32` type to unsigned.\n2. CUTLASS MoE can be run from `compressed_tensors.py` either with PPLX or without it. If we run with PPLX, we end up running `CutlassExpertsFp8`'s forward function which takes different arguments than a straightforward non-PPLX `cutlass_moe_fp8` call. On the current main, this results in errors when running with PPLX. Fixing this issue also makes it easier to bring back pre-computed strides in [PR20762](https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/20762).\n\n#### Testing:\n\nPPLX run:\n```\nexport MASTER_ADDR=127.0.0.1\nexport MASTER_PORT=29500\nexport VLLM_ALL2ALL_BACKEND=pplx\npython3 examples/offline_inference/data_parallel.py \\\n        --model=\"nm-testing/DeepSeek-Coder-V2-Lite-Instruct-FP8\" \\\n        --dp-size=2 \\\n        --tp-size=1 \\\n        --trust-remote-code\n```\n\nNon-PPLX run: run inference with `LLM(model=\"nm-testing/DeepSeek-Coder-V2-Lite-Instruct-FP8\")`",
    "created_at": "2025-07-11T15:40:14Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-07-13T02:39:15Z",
